==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Growl
<hw>Growl</hw> <pr>(groul)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Growled</conjf> <pr>(grould)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Growling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[D. <ets>grollen</ets>
to grunt, murmur, be angry; akin to G. <ets>grollen</ets> to be
angry.]</ety> <def>To utter a deep guttural sound, as an angry dog; to
give forth an angry, grumbling sound.</def> <rj><au>Gay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Growl</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Growl
<hw>Growl</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To express by growling.</def>
<rj><au>Thomson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Growl</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Growl
<hw>Growl</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The deep, threatening sound made by a
surly dog; a grumbling sound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Growler</ent>⟦br⟧
